20_18	0.5714285714285714	Help! Colorado potato beetles are destroying my potato plants.
20_19	0.0	I've been trying to go the organic route, handpicking them every day.
20_20	0.0	It's not working.
20_21	0.0	If I don't do something soon, I'm afraid the plants will die.
20_22	0.0	&QL; A.
20_23	0.4166666666666667	Leptinotarsa decemlineata, to give the miserable creature its proper name, is among the most difficult garden pests to control, organically or otherwise.
20_24	0.0	Don't panic.
20_25	0.0	Potato plants can take a lot of defoliation and still produce a decent crop.
20_26	0.0	But do take action, employing multiple strategies for best results.
20_27	0.8	Start by applying a dose of the organic gardener's friend, Bacillus thuringiensis var.
20_28	0.6666666666666666	san diego (or var.
20_29	0.0	tenebrionis). It is effective at killing small larvae, though only after they've consumed some of it.
20_30	0.0	This means spraying thoroughly (and repeatedly) according to the directions that come with the stuff.
20_31	0.0	It also means you're still stuck with larger larvae and adults.
20_32	0.7	Those can be killed with rotenone, a comparatively mild botanical poison permitted for use by organic gardeners.
20_33	0.0	Neem extract (Azadirachtin) is also on the organic list.
20_34	0.0	Well-stocked garden centers and farm supply stores will usually have these products.
20_35	0.0	Handpicking is still very useful, if it includes crushing the clusters of bright orange-yellow eggs that hide under the leaves.
20_36	0.0	It costs nothing, it doesn't pollute or kill any other creatures.
20_37	0.2	It keeps populations down and soothes gardeners, who if they have potato beetles, also have frustrations and aggressions that need release.
20_38	0.0	Unfortunately, it's not perfect.
20_39	0.0	No matter how thorough you are, you always miss a few, and you don't have to miss many to lose the war.
20_40	0.0	A single female can have 10,000 decendants by the end of summer.
20_41	0.0	One advantage (for the beetles) of numbers like these is the chance at resistant mutations.
20_42	0.0	No matter which controls you use, a few will be resistant, and those few will be multitudes ere long.
20_43	0.0	That's why it's important to attack on several fronts.
20_44	0.36363636363636365	To add insult to infestation, Colorado potato beetles can live a full two years.
20_45	0.0	But they won't stay around where there's nothing to eat, so the final, or first, line of defense is late planting.
20_46	0.0	If they don't find any potato, eggplant or nicotiana leaves when they emerge from the ground in spring, they'll leave.
20_47	0.0	More will appear, but if you can thwart that first wave, subsequent ones will be much smaller.
