21_5	0.0	Colorful, easy, reliable and pest-free are not bad adjectives, and if the marigold is more often thought of as common than as choice, those qualities may explain why.
21_6	0.0	There is much good to say about a flower with a sunny disposition and a desire to please.
21_7	0.0	In August, when most perennials are in their summer sulk and the annual flower garden looks a bit ratty, marigolds can be counted on to look presentable.
21_8	0.0	The season is long, and fidelity in a flower is as praiseworthy as flamboyance.
21_9	0.0	They don't look any different than they did in late June _ mounds of roly-poly flowers in shades of orange, yellow and sort-of red _ but marigolds look good when their neighbors are starting to fade.
21_10	0.0	Indeed, it would be nice to be an iris in one's youth and a marigold in middle age.
